\n*\n\nYou all were lied to\nmarket dynamics don\u0027t work the way as they were interpreted for the \"retail sociaty\" in the past years especially after gamestop gamma squeeze where plp started to know about options market, then came Cem Karsan with his vanna/charm flows, and in the twitter space came vol sig and OD and started to explain actual things\nbut the explainations based on these naive models, zero gammas, IVs etc. are all mumble jumble, and you better forget about it, in order to be able to get new knowledge. If you are here to share the same things, i have a bad news for you.. :/ you won\u0027t learn anything.\nIf you click on the chat tab left, you can see my chat about OptionsDepth. There i went ahead and explained Gamma, Vanna and Charm in simply terms. read that, take the time to think on that. \nlets see some concepts, and vomma crus\n\nZERO GAMMA \nif you look at any GEX charts I provide, or at OD heatmaps, you will see multiple zero gamma lines. Every value that can go from positive to negative and vice versa can be zero too. Charm, vanna, vomma, rho, parmicharm, anything... The misconception arises from that in naive GEX models the assumption is used that customers sell calls and buy puts. So they handle the OI that way, and they will get a gamma profile like this one:\n*\nnow in a chart like this speed is always net positive, consequently vanna/charm flows are always net supportive, spot/vol beta is always net negative and its always left-tail risk\nnow, the concept of zero gamma is that thats where market makers shift from bullish to bearish and bearish to bullish.... this is what you heard, right? bcs negative gamma makes them hedge into the direction, and positive gamma makes them to hedge against it.\nnow, they assign bearishness to negative gamma bcs negative gamma is always to the downside, and positive gamma is always to the downside and once the price reached negative gamma territory, price will freefall\nzero gamma and gamma flip is the same for some plp and not the same for some others.. dunno about that no consensus also, they do the same with vanna called VEX at some lvl they get negative vanna, some other lvls they get positive vanna... based on OI, and they say like negative vanna repells the price, positive vnana attracts it... etc. you know AND ALL OF THESE THINGS ARE BULLSHIT! you have to forget about all of this, change your mind in order to REALLY understand how it works\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ: Here\u0027s a question: considering only gamma, and excluding all the other variables...if the MM\u0027s are long 6050 and no other positions... they hedge ATM the delta 0.50. if price goes to 6060 the keep hedging a bit more, bc delta is higher, then 6070, same thing, a bit more hedge. yes?\nnow at 6070 suddenly they become neg. gamma at 6070 in addition to their previous 6050 position. the 6070 neg. gamma would halt their sell hedging of 6050 yes?\nassuming the size at 6050 and 6070 are the same essentially I\u0027m just trying to understand how positive gamma hedging acts when in a rising market MM\u0027s start approaching neg. gamma level not trying to be exacting...so did i explain it broadly correct?\n"},{"ty":"as","st":"document","si":0,"ei":0,"sm":{"ds_pw":595.3,"ds_mt":42.55,"ds_lhs":1,"ds_mr":56.7,"ds_mb":56.7,"ds_rtd":"mso-rtd.0","ds_ulhfl":false,"ds_ml":56.7,"ds_mh":35.4,"ds_ph":841.9,"ds_mf":35.4}},{"ty":"ae","et":"inline","id":"i.0","epm":{"ee_eo":{"eo_bo":{"ln_s":0,"ln_w":0.0,"ln_c2":{"hclr_color":"#000000","clr_type":0}},"i_pid":null,"eo_mb":0.0,"i_ht":244.65,"eo_rtdf":{"rdf_ft":0},"eo_ml":0.0,"eo_mr":0.0,"eo_ad":null,"i_cid":"s-blob-v1-IMAGE-N16Ma-J_GzQ","i_cont":0.0,"eo_mt":0.0,"eo_type":0,"eo_lco":{"lc_oi":"","lc_cs":"","lc_ct":0,"lc_sci":"","lc_srk":""},"i_wth":481.9,"eo_at":null,"i_iwc":{"iwc_w":false},"eo_hb":false,"eo_rtd":"","i_crop":{"crop_oxr":-0.0,"crop_oyr":-0.0,"crop_rot":0.0,"crop_hr":1.0,"crop_wr":1.0},"i_iw":false,"i_rot":0.0,"i_clst":{"cv":{"op":"set","opValue":