ot moves up, you have to BUY 5 more shares of stock. buying this time. \nquick math: if you are long ATM put: you have -50 delta, you long 50 shares of stock. in positive gamma exposure, lets say you long 2 gamma, if spot moves up by one unit, you will have -50 + 2 \u003d -48 delta to hedge, you only need to hedge 48 delta, so you sell 2 shares of stock now, in negative gamma exposure, if you would have short that 2 gamma, if spot moves up by one unit, you would have -50 + -2 \u003d -52, so you would have buy 2 more shares of stocks. if you are long ATM call: you long 50 delta, you short 50 shares of stock, long 2 gamma, spot up: 50 + 2 \u003d 52, sell 2 shares of stock short 2 gamma, spot up: 50 -2 \u003d 48, buy back 2 shares of stock. same thing happens with calls and puts\nQ:how constantly does a mm hedge his position in the real world?\nA: they must be directional risk neutral, they play for trading revenue... they hedge on a very high frequency\nQ:When you are making the gex profile like in yesterdays example are you just looking at 0DTE gex? Or all expiration weighted\nA: All. \n\none thing, and this is very important. if you read my posts, you can see how i think about the market. dealer flow is only one part of the puzzle. however, the whole market is revolving around over- and underpricing the odds. this is what its all about, and this is what will tell the next step. then the anomalies I wrote about in my educational post. dealer flow is a reactive/reflexive thing, a response to the customer flows. shouldn\u0027t be overemphatized\nThis is most important I think, levels keep leveling but key is understanding the flow and sticking with it . \nYes. This is why i advised to read about gambling strategies. thats the primal thing to understand. dealer flow is just an addition, it shades the pic more, and more accurate. you can see the reflexive natures... but you know, lets say, you see the MM long risk reversal positioning, you pre-project all the gamma, hamma, jamma, kamma, etc. you do the simulation, but then boom, suddenly a big customer comes and sells a butterfly? the whole profile is messed up now\n*\nQ: Alma what is the framework / consept you use in order to decide if you will trade 0DTE, or longer exp ?\nA: theta profile usually, and the expected vol. if vol is low, i don\u0027t like 0dte, perhaps not even trade that day\nread more here https://x.com/alma18499/status/1865396323828297984\n"},{"ty":"ae","et":"inline","id":"i.3","epm":{"ee_eo":{"eo_bo":{"ln_s":0,"ln_w":0.0,"ln_c2":{"hclr_color":"#000000","clr_type":0}},"i_pid":null,"eo_mb":0.0,"i_ht":139.1,"eo_rtdf":{"rdf_ft":0},"eo_ml":0.0,"eo_mr":0.0,"eo_ad":null,"i_cid":"s-blob-v1-IMAGE-H-67yH29d1s","i_cont":0.0,"eo_mt":0.0,"eo_type":0,"eo_lco":{"lc_oi":"","lc_cs":"","lc_ct":0,"lc_sci":"","lc_srk":""},"i_wth":481.9,"eo_at":null,"i_iwc":{"iwc_w":false},"eo_hb":false,"eo_rtd":"","i_crop":{"crop_oxr":-0.0,"crop_oyr":-0.0,"crop_rot":0.0,"crop_hr":1.0,"crop_wr":1.0},"i_iw":false,"i_rot":0.0,"i_clst":{"cv":{"op":"set","opValue":[]}},"i_bri":0.0,"i_msct":0,"i_src":null,"i_opa":1.0}}},{"ty":"te","id":"i.3","spi":7255},{"ty":"as","st":"paragraph","si":4154,"ei":4154,"sm":{"ps_klt_i":true,"ps_awao_i":true,"ps_sm_i":true,"ps_ls_i":true,"ps_il_i":true,"ps_ir_i":true,"ps_al_i":true,"ps_bl_i":true,"ps_sd_i":true,"ps_sb_i":true,"ps_sa_i":true,"ps_lslm_i":true,"ps_br_i":true,"ps_bbtw_i":true,"ps_kwn_i":true,"ps_bt_i":true,"ps_ifl_i":true,"ps_bb_i":true,"ps_pbb_i":true}},{"ty":"as","st":"paragraph","si":4936,"ei":4936,"sm":{"ps_klt_i":true,"ps_awao_i":true,"ps_sm_i":true,"ps_ls_i":true,"ps_il_i":true,"ps_ir_i":true,"ps_al_i":true,"ps_bl_i":true,"ps_sd_i":true,"ps_sb_i":true,"ps_sa_i":true,"ps_lslm_i":true,"ps_br_i":true,"ps_bbtw_i":true,"ps_kwn_i":true,"ps_bt_i":true,"ps_ifl_i":true,"ps_bb_i":true,"ps_pbb_i":true}},{"ty":"as","st":"paragraph","si":5212,"ei":5212,"sm":{"ps_klt_i":true,"ps_awao_i":true,"ps_sm_i":true,"ps_ls_i":true,"ps_il_i":true,"ps_ir_i":true,"ps_al_i":true,"ps